External knowledge:
- A higher average success rate indicates better performance; 
- A larger number of completed tests indicates more reliable results.

- Success rate refers to the percentage of successful test runs; 
- Improvement (I) is denoted by the letter 'I' in the success rate, which should be excluded when calculating average success rate for completed runs;
- Resolution rate refers to the percentage of resolved anomalies.
